---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About -- creator.blog" description="About creator.blog and the person behind it.">
  <style>
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
    }
    ul {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  </style>

  <h1>About creator.blog</h1>

  <p>I started creator.blog because I needed a resource like this and could not find one. Most content about "being a creator" is either too vague to be useful or too focused on selling you a $997 course.</p>

  <p>What I wanted was straightforward, practical information. Which AI tools are actually worth paying for? How do you grow a newsletter from zero without a huge social following? What does a realistic solo creator tech stack look like in 2026?</p>

  <p>So I started writing the answers myself.</p>

  <h2>What You Will Find Here</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>AI tool reviews</strong> based on actual use in my workflow, not press releases</li>
    <li><strong>Newsletter growth guides</strong> drawn from building my own email lists</li>
    <li><strong>Creator business frameworks</strong> for people who work alone and prefer it that way</li>
    <li><strong>Automation workflows</strong> that save real hours, not theoretical minutes</li>
    <li><strong>Tech stack breakdowns</strong> comparing platforms, tools, and services for solo operators</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Approach</h2>

  <p>Every recommendation comes from hands-on experience. I test tools in my own projects before writing about them. I track what actually moves the needle versus what just feels productive. And I always mention the free or cheaper alternative when one exists.</p>

  <p>No sponsored content. No affiliate-first reviews. Just honest, practical guides for people building content businesses with modern tools.</p>
</BaseLayout>
